    public interface InputVisitor<R>
    A visitor for Inputs This visitor is used to create the actual UI elements and handle the parsing logic. So Inputs need to implement one of the options. As some of the target types are interfaces there may be classes that implement more than one target. It is the implemented accept method that defines which option is used to create the forms.
